		    </li>
		    <li class="question">
		    	<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="$(this).parent().find('.answer').toggle()">My school is not participating in the Design for Change Contest what can we do?</a>
		    	<div class="answer" style="display: none">
				    You can take on the initiative by yourself, as an individual or as a group. Forward the Design for Change URL to teachers who you believe could make good mentors for your project.
		    	</div>
		    </li>
		    <li class="question">
		    	<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="$(this).parent().find('.answer').toggle()">Can a group of friends from different schools participate in the Design Challenge?</a>
		    	<div class="answer" style="display: none">
					Yes!
		    	</div>
		    </li>
		    <li class="question">
		    	<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="$(this).parent().find('.answer').toggle()">Can I get my school to participate in the Design for Change Contest?</a>
		    	<div class="answer" style="display: none">
				    Approach your teacher, principal or head of school, if they haven't already registered. Log on to the website, register, download the toolkit or request it to be sent to you (if it already hasn't been sent to your school).</p>
		    	</div>
		    </li>
		    <li class="question">
		    	<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="$(this).parent().find('.answer').toggle()">How do I get my school to participate in the contest?</a>
		    	<div class="answer" style="display: none">
				    Approach your teacher, principal or head of school, if they haven't already registered. Log on to the website, register, and then download the toolkit or request.
		    	</div>
		    </li>
		    <li class="question">
		    	<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="$(this).parent().find('.answer').toggle()">Will you give me promotional material to put up on the notice board?</a>
		    	<div class="answer" style="display: none">
